{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"67215e28-78b6-443a-916e-43d247a4dd2d","title":"Setup","desc":"","updated":1613464414649,"created":1613464405744,"custom":{},"fname":"pi.setup","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":".","name":"vault","selfContained":true},"contentHash":"d3eaddd1806ab3d7ac35583a8b899ea0","links":[],"anchors":{"setting-up-the-raspberri-pi":{"type":"header","text":"Setting up the Raspberri Pi","value":"setting-up-the-raspberri-pi","line":8,"column":0,"depth":1},"setup-steps":{"type":"header","text":"Setup Steps","value":"setup-steps","line":10,"column":0,"depth":2},"enable-ssh":{"type":"header","text":"Enable SSH","value":"enable-ssh","line":18,"column":0,"depth":2},"installing-docker":{"type":"header","text":"Installing Docker","value":"installing-docker","line":21,"column":0,"depth":2},"uninstalling-docker":{"type":"header","text":"Uninstalling Docker","value":"uninstalling-docker","line":28,"column":0,"depth":2}},"children":[],"parent":"f80d45a1-bd90-4097-96bc-0301fbc4d937","data":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"setup\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#setup\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Setup</h1>\n<h1 id=\"setting-up-the-raspberri-pi\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#setting-up-the-raspberri-pi\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Setting up the Raspberri Pi</h1>\n<h2 id=\"setup-steps\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#setup-steps\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Setup Steps</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Flash SD card</li>\n<li>Enable ssh following the instructions below</li>\n<li>Change password using <code>passwd</code> for the pi user</li>\n<li>Set the country using <code>raspi-config</code> in the locale options select <code>en_GB.UTF-8</code> and <code>en_US.UTF-8</code></li>\n<li>Install vim <code>sudo apt install vim</code></li>\n<li>Install docker </li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"enable-ssh\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#enable-ssh\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Enable SSH</h2>\n<p>SSH is disabled by default, enable this by adding an empty file named <code>ssh</code> to the boot partition of the SD card (this is the only folder that will appear to Windows)</p>\n<h2 id=\"installing-docker\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#installing-docker\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Installing Docker</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Update and upgrade <code>sudo apt-get update &#x26;&#x26; sudo apt-get upgrade -y</code></li>\n<li>Download install script <code>curl -fsSL https://get.docker.com -o get-docker.sh</code> and execute <code>sudo sh get-docker.sh</code></li>\n<li>Add <code>pi</code> user to the docker group <code>sudo usermod -aG docker pi</code> (log out and in for changes to take place)</li>\n<li>Check docker version and info: <code>docker version</code> and <code>docker info</code></li>\n<li>Run hello world test container <code>docker run hello-world</code></li>\n</ol>\n<h2 id=\"uninstalling-docker\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#uninstalling-docker\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Uninstalling Docker</h2>\n<p>Delete using package manager:\n<code>sudo apt-get purge docker-ce</code>\nRemove leftover images, containers, volumes and other data:\n<code>sudo rm -rf /var/lib/docker</code></p>","noteIndex":{"id":"root","title":"root","desc":"","updated":1595961348801,"created":1595961348801,"custom":{"nav_order":0,"permalink":"/"},"fname":"root","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":".","name":"vault","selfContained":true},"contentHash":"dad9815845eec627c937e34281a065d5","links":[],"anchors":{"root":{"type":"header","text":"Root","value":"root","line":8,